    <div class="content-head">Graduate Student Researcher, Department of Computer Science  <span class="smallHead"> | UC Irvine, Irvine, CA, USA</span></div>
    <div class="content">
      <p>From 09/2005 to 09/2007:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Contributed in studying the free-rider exploit in BitTorrent peer-to-peer network using the PlanetLab overlay network</li>
        <li>Contributed in the design of a MANET routing protocol using Bloom filter data structure for anonymous routing</li>
     </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="content-head">Product Engineer, Telco Home Network Business Unit <span class="smallHead"> | <a href="http://www.cisco.com"> Cisco Systems</a>, Irvine, CA, USA</span></div>
    <div class="content">
      <p>From 4/2006 to 2/2011:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Product Engineer who assisted at first and was later in charge of product development life cycle for <a href="http://www.cisco.com/en/US/products/ps8426/index.html"> Linksys WCM300</a>, the world's fastest cable modem at the time with eight downstream channel bonding and DOCSIS 3.0 compliant </li>
        <i> (the product was an endpoint unit of the DOCSIS Downstream Wideband Architecture and Winner of the 2007 Cisco Pioneer Hall of Fame Award for the Core Technology Category) </i> 
	<li>Product Engineer that facilitated the product development life cycle of several mobile broadband routers for the service provider market (Linksys WRT54G3Gv1/WRT54G3Gv2)</li>
     </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="content-head">Software Development Engineer, CDMA ASIC Software Group <span class="smallHead"> | <a href="http://www.qualcomm.com"> Qualcomm</a>, San Diego, CA, USA</span></div>
    <div class="content">
      <p>From 6/2003 to 9/2005:</p>
      <ul>
	<li>Software development for short messaging services protocol stack with 3GPP and TIA/EIA communication standard compliance</li>
	<li>Coordinated development process with design reviews, software developers, and system team for integration and testing</li>
	<li>Provided technology and product leadership in short messaging services with patent filing and customer interaction to ensure timely product delivery and passing GCF and CDG certification </li>
        <li>Designed and prototyped mobile user interfaces for various messaging applications </li>
